Usage: define_property [-help] <property_name> [-lower_bound <string>]
                       -object_type <string> [-string_values <string>]
                       -type <string> [-upper_bound <string>]

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
<property_name>           # Name of property (string, required)
-lower_bound <string>     # Lower range of type int, float, double
                          # (string, optional)
-object_type <string>     # Type of object on which property is to be defined.
                          # Types can be design, port, cell, pin, net, lib,
                          # lib_cell, lib_pin (string, required)
-string_values <string>   # Values which can be given for type string
                          # (string, optional)
-type <string>            # Type of property. Type can be string, int, float,
                          # double, boolean (string, required)
-upper_bound <string>     # Upper  range of type int, float, double
                          # (string, optional)